The title race between Liverpool and Manchester City has gone to the wire. We look at the figures as the two sides battle it out for the Premier League crown. City top the table with 90 points, one point ahead of Liverpool. The league leaders have won 28 of their games, one more than the Reds. Liverpool have however lost fewer games, one less than City's three loses even though City have a superior goal difference (72) against Liverpool's 66. City have drawn six games, two less than Liverpool's eight.